        <h2>2.2 Introduction</h2>

        <div class="icon_intro">
            <p>
                The clinical course of MS varies considerably between different individuals. 
                This can present problems in the identification of the type of MS as individuals 
                rarely fit neatly into categories; this also has repercussions for the person with 
                MS themselves. For example, even if diagnosed with a certain type of MS, there 
                is no guarantee that any individual’s disease will follow the same course as another’s 
                with the same type: there may be wide differences in disability and functional 
                difficulties between individuals<sup>1</sup>.
            </p>
